 If you need to run a task only occasionally, like resizing an image when a user uploads it paying for a server to run 24/7 is a waste of money and maintenance effort.

 AWS Lambda solves this by introducing serverless computing. It runs your code only when needed, scales automatically, and charges you only for the milliseconds used.

 # what is lambda function?
 The code that you want Lambda to run is known as a Lambda function.
 A serverless compute service that runs your code automatically in response to events without managing servers.
 You upload code → AWS runs it when triggered.

# What is function?
A Lambda Function is your code packaged and deployed to Lambda.

It contains:
Code (index.js / index.mjs)
Runtime (Node.js, Python, etc.)
Configuration (memory, timeout, IAM role)

# what is runtime?
The programming environment Lambda uses to execute your code.

Examples:
Node.js 18.x
Python 3.12
Java 17

# what is handler?
The entry point of your function.

export const handler = async (event) => { }

# what is Invocation?
When Lambda executes your function, it is called an invocation.

# what is Event?
An event is the JSON data sent to Lambda when it is triggered.

